// VS Code REST Client file: install 'REST Client' extension to use
@host = http://localhost:3000

### Health
GET {{host}}/health

### Create user (raw SQL or via DB tool; here we assume a user exists with id 1)
# You can insert manually:
# INSERT INTO users (email, name) VALUES ('user@example.com', 'Krunal');

### Create product
POST {{host}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "SKU-1001",
  "name": "Phone Charger",
  "price_cents": 1299,
  "stock": 25
}

### List products (cached)
GET {{host}}/products?page=1&limit=10&min_price=500&max_price=2000&in_stock=true

### Create order
POST {{host}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": 1,
  "items": [
    { "product_id": 1, "qty": 2 }
  ]
}

### Get order by id
GET {{host}}/orders/1

### Cancel order
PATCH {{host}}/orders/1/cancel
